  ---
  How KU Markdown Sync Works

  The Flow:

  1. MARKDOWN FILE (your vault)
     ---
     uid: ku.python.functions
     title: Python Functions
     domain: tech
     connections:
       requires: ["ku.python.basics"]
       enables: ["ku.python.decorators"]
     ---
     # Content here...

  2. PARSE (MarkdownSyncService._parse_knowledge_unit)
     - Extracts YAML frontmatter
     - Creates KnowledgeUnit dataclass
     - Stores connections in metadata._connections

  3. RELATIONSHIP CONFIG (defines how YAML → Neo4j edges)
     rel_config = {
         "connections.requires": {
             "rel_type": "PREREQUISITE",
             "target_label": "Ku",
             "direction": "incoming"  # (n)<-[:PREREQUISITE]-(target)
         },
         "connections.enables": {
             "rel_type": "ENABLES",
             "target_label": "Ku",
             "direction": "outgoing"  # (n)-[:ENABLES]->(target)
         }
     }

  4. BULK INGESTION (BulkIngestionEngine.upsert_with_relationships)
     - Creates (ku:Ku {uid: "ku.python.functions", ...})
     - Creates edges: (ku)<-[:PREREQUISITE]-(ku.python.basics)
     - Creates edges: (ku)-[:ENABLES]->(ku.python.decorators)

