  What MOC Markdown Sync Would Need

  Following the same pattern, a MOC markdown file would look like:

  ---
  moc: true
  uid: moc.python.fundamentals
  title: Python Fundamentals
  domain: tech
  visibility: private

  # Direct content references (top-level, no section)
  contains:
    knowledge: ["ku.python.basics", "ku.python.functions"]
    paths: ["lp.python.beginner"]
    principles: ["principle.practice-daily"]

  # Practice recommendations
  recommends:
    habits: ["habit.coding.daily-practice"]
    tasks: ["task.setup.python-env"]
    events: ["event.weekly.code-review"]

  # Cross-domain bridges
  bridges:
    - uid: ku.math.logic
      domain: math
    - uid: goal.career.developer
      domain: personal

  # Related MOCs
  related_mocs: ["moc.programming.basics", "moc.python.advanced"]
  ---

